<h2>Key Factors for Solar ROI</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Electricity Rate:</strong> Higher = more savings. States over $0.15/kWh see excellent ROI.</li>
<li><strong>Sun Hours:</strong> More sun = more production. Even cloudy states work with high rates.</li>
<li><strong>Federal Tax Credit:</strong> 30% ITC applies everywhere through 2032.</li>
<li><strong>State Incentives:</strong> SC (25%), IA (15%), NM (10%) stack on federal.</li>
<li><strong>Net Metering:</strong> Full retail rate (CA, MA, NJ) maximizes savings.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2026 Federal Solar Tax Credit</h2>
<p>The 30% Investment Tax Credit (ITC) on system cost runs through 2032. On a $20K system, that's $6K credit.</p>
